<article id="post-538" class="post-538 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-travel tag-around-the-world tag-russia tag-trans-siberian-railway tag-yekaterinburg">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/a-little-story-about-ekaterinburg/" rel="bookmark">A little story about Ekaterinburg</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Ekaterinburg (Soviet name, a much harsher &#8220;Sverdlovsk&#8221;) is a wonderful little place to spend an afternoon. Assuming you can find your hotel, that is.<br />
After doing our little thing at the post office to try and catch up on postings, Amy and I did about the only thing we had time for: a walking tour. Fortunately, our Lonely Planet book on the Trans Siberian Railway has a walking tour laid out pretty well. It was just a matter for us to walk it.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/a-little-story-about-ekaterinburg/#more-538" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;A little story about Ekaterinburg&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/a-little-story-about-ekaterinburg/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2005-05-13T06:20:26-06:00">13 May 2005</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/around-the-world/" rel="tag">around the world</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/russia/" rel="tag">russia</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/trans-siberian-railway/" rel="tag">trans-siberian railway</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/yekaterinburg/" rel="tag">yekaterinburg</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/a-little-story-about-ekaterinburg/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on A little story about Ekaterinburg</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
