<article id="post-525" class="post-525 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants category-travel tag-around-the-world tag-russia tag-st-petersburg">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/pickpockets-suck/" rel="bookmark">Pickpockets suck!</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><cite>[This entry originally posted on <a href="http://www.howtogetlost.com/">How To Get Lost</a>: <a href="http://www.howtogetlost.com/2005/05/05/pickpockets-suck/">Pickpockets suck!</a>.]</cite><br />
I&#8217;ve had two separate and unique run-ins with pickpockets. The first was at the Edgefest concert in Vancouver back in &#8220;99. I think we were listening to Sloan at the time, and some idiot came up behind me, dragging his finger up the back pocket in a vain attempt to pop whatever was in there (which was nothing) out. I should have reacted at the time, but never having been picked before, I wasn&#8217;t sure what to do.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/pickpockets-suck/#more-525" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Pickpockets suck!&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
